&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/zhuqi-lucas"&gt;Qi Zhu&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href="https://www.massive.com/"&gt;Massive&lt;/a&gt;); &lt;a href="https://github.com/alamb"&gt;Andrew Lamb&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href="https://www.influxdata.com/"&gt;InfluxData&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://datafusion.apache.org/"&gt;Apache DataFusion&lt;/a&gt; uses sortedness automatically — even when data is only
partially sorted or when no ordering was declared. This post explains how
plan-time sort pushdown, runtime scan reordering, and row-group pruning driven
by &lt;a href="https://datafusion.apache.org/blog/2025/09/10/dynamic-filters/"&gt;dynamic filters&lt;/a&gt; make that possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="are-real-datasets-sorted"&gt;Are Real Datasets Sorted?&lt;a class="headerlink" href="#are-real-datasets-sorted" title="Permanent link"&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
